# Blue Dragon Documentation

Welcome to the documentation for Blue Dragon, an open-source project developed by MySillyDreams. Blue Dragon is a collection of commonly used UI elements and functionalities designed to expedite the development process. This documentation provides a comprehensive guide on integrating and using Blue Dragon in your projects.

## Table of Contents

1. [Installation](#installation)
2. [Usage](#usage)
3. [Customization](#customization)
4. [Contributing](#contributing)
5. [License](#license)

## Installation

To start using Blue Dragon in your project, follow these steps:

1. Clone the Blue Dragon repository:

   ```shell
   git clone https://github.com/MySillyDreams/BlueDragon.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

   ```shell
   cd BlueDragon
   ```

3. Copy the desired UI elements and functionalities from the `dist` folder to your project directory.

4. Include the necessary CSS and JavaScript files in your HTML file:

   ```html
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/blue-dragon.css">
   <script src="path/to/blue-dragon.js"></script>
   ```

   Replace `"path/to/blue-dragon.css"` and `"path/to/blue-dragon.js"` with the actual paths to the copied files.

5. You're now ready to use Blue Dragon in your project!

